<title>GERMANY: Bayer to step up investment plans in Asia.</title>
<headline>Bayer to step up investment plans in Asia.</headline>
<dateline>LEVERKUSEN 1997-02-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>The top executive at Bayer AG said the German chemicals group will step up its investment plans in Asia earlier than expected to more than two billion marks ($1.2 billion) during the next five years.</p>
<p>Bayer chief executive Manfred Schneider told journalists at a company event late on Wednesday that some of the funds had been earmarked for a polycarbonate plant in Thailand and a polyurethane plant in Taiwan.</p>
<p>Additional funds would also be spent to increase research in the region.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525 ($ = 1.688 German Marks)</p>
